{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-tsx","path":"/physics/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Fundamental Terms of Physics</h1>\n<p><strong>Energy</strong> is the ability to do work. <strong>Work</strong> is the energy transferred to an object that causes a displacement. A <strong>displacement</strong> is the measure of the distance moved in a specific direction, or the shortest distance from an initial to a final position.</p>\n<p><img src=\"../img/distance-vs-displacement.svg\" alt=\"Distance vs. Displacement\"></p>\n<p>Work is most commonly measured in joules (<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>J</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">J</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span></span></span></span>). One <strong>joule</strong> is equal to the energy required for one newton (<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span></span></span></span>) to perform a displacement of one meter (<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span>), or <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>J</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>N</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">J=Nm</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>Newtons are a measurement of force. One <strong>newton</strong> is the force required to accelerate one kilogram (<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">kg</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span></span></span></span>) one meter per second squared, or <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>∗</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow><msup><mi>s</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N = \\frac{kg*m}{s^2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.277216em;vertical-align:-0.345em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.9322159999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.6550000000000002em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7463142857142857em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.786em;margin-right:0.07142857142857144em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.446108em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">∗</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">m</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.345em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<h2>Video: How Much Energy is 1 Joule?</h2>\n<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/_qEBElHoYUA\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<h2>Physics Resources</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://physics.info/\">The Physics Hypertextbook</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/physics/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Physics","tags":[]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/physics/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2270328656","3794076007","80858887"]}